<!-- COSTS & ARCHITECTURE -->
<div class="page-break"></div>
<h1 id="costs">1. Costs &amp; Architecture Overview</h1>

<h3>Monthly Costs</h3>
<table>
    <tr><th>Item</th><th>Cost</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Hetzner CX32 (4 vCPU, 8GB RAM, 80GB SSD)</td><td>&euro;8.57/mo (~$10)</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Domain (e.g. bankos.ng or .com)</td><td>~$15/yr</td></tr>
    <tr><td>SSL (Let's Encrypt)</td><td>Free</td></tr>
    <tr><td>SMTP (Brevo free tier &mdash; 300 emails/day)</td><td>Free</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td><strong>~$10/month</strong></td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Server Architecture</h3>
<pre>
Hetzner CX32 (Ubuntu 22.04)
&#9500;&#9472;&#9472; Nginx (reverse proxy + SSL)
&#9474;   &#9500;&#9472;&#9472; admin.yourdomain.com    &#8594; bankos (Admin Portal)
&#9474;   &#9500;&#9472;&#9472; app.yourdomain.com      &#8594; bankos-portal (Customer Portal)
&#9474;   &#9492;&#9472;&#9472; super.yourdomain.com    &#8594; bankos-superadmin (Super Admin)
&#9500;&#9472;&#9472; PHP 8.1-FPM (3 pools)
&#9500;&#9472;&#9472; PostgreSQL 15
&#9500;&#9472;&#9472; Redis (sessions + cache + queues)
&#9492;&#9472;&#9472; Supervisor (queue workers)
</pre>

<!-- PHASE 1 -->
<div class="page-break"></div>
<h1 id="phase1">2. Phase 1 &mdash; Create &amp; Access Server</h1>

<h3>1.1 Create Hetzner Account &amp; Server</h3>
<ol>
    <li>Go to <strong>hetzner.com/cloud</strong> and sign up</li>
    <li>Create new project &rarr; Add Server:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Location:</strong> Helsinki or Falkenstein (cheapest)</li>
            <li><strong>Image:</strong> Ubuntu 22.04</li>
            <li><strong>Type:</strong> CX32 (4 vCPU, 8GB RAM, 80GB SSD)</li>
            <li><strong>SSH Key:</strong> Skip this &mdash; don't add one</li>
            <li><strong>Name:</strong> bankos-prod</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Hetzner will email you the <strong>root password</strong> to your registered email</li>
</ol>

<h3>1.2 Connect to Server</h3>
<p>Download and install <strong>PuTTY</strong> (putty.org) or use Windows Terminal:</p>
<pre>
ssh root@YOUR_SERVER_IP
# It will ask: "Are you sure you want to continue connecting?" &rarr; type: yes
# Enter the root password from Hetzner's email
# It will force you to change the password &mdash; pick a strong one and SAVE IT
</pre>

<div class="important">
    <strong>Important:</strong> From this point, every command below is typed inside this SSH session.
</div>

<!-- PHASE 2 -->
<h1 id="phase2">3. Phase 2 &mdash; Server Security &amp; Setup</h1>

<h3>2.1 Create a deploy user (don't run apps as root)</h3>
<pre>
adduser deploy
# Set a password when prompted &mdash; SAVE THIS PASSWORD TOO
</pre>
<pre>
usermod -aG sudo deploy
</pre>

<h3>2.2 Allow password SSH login</h3>
<p>Already enabled by default on Hetzner, but confirm:</p>
<pre>
nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config
</pre>
<p>Find and make sure these lines say:</p>
<pre>
PermitRootLogin yes
PasswordAuthentication yes
</pre>
<p>Save: <code>Ctrl+O</code>, <code>Enter</code>, <code>Ctrl+X</code></p>
<pre>
systemctl restart sshd
</pre>

<h3>2.3 Firewall</h3>
<pre>
ufw allow OpenSSH
ufw allow 80
ufw allow 443
ufw --force enable
</pre>

<h3>2.4 Test deploy user login</h3>
<p>Open a <strong>NEW</strong> terminal window:</p>
<pre>
ssh deploy@YOUR_SERVER_IP
# Enter the deploy user password
# If this works, you're good. Close this test window.
</pre>

<!-- PHASE 3 -->
<div class="page-break"></div>
<h1 id="phase3">4. Phase 3 &mdash; Install Software Stack</h1>
<p>Run all of these as <strong>root</strong> (the first SSH window):</p>

<h3>3.1 Update system</h3>
<pre>
apt update &amp;&amp; apt upgrade -y
</pre>

<h3>3.2 Install PHP 8.1</h3>
<pre>
apt install -y software-properties-common
add-apt-repository ppa:ondrej/php -y
apt update
apt install -y php8.1 php8.1-fpm php8.1-pgsql php8.1-mbstring \
  php8.1-xml php8.1-bcmath php8.1-curl php8.1-zip php8.1-intl \
  php8.1-redis php8.1-gd php8.1-readline
</pre>

<h3>3.3 Install Composer</h3>
<pre>
curl -sS https://getcomposer.org/installer | php
mv composer.phar /usr/local/bin/composer
</pre>

<h3>3.4 Install PostgreSQL 15</h3>
<pre>
apt install -y postgresql-15 postgresql-client-15
systemctl enable postgresql
systemctl start postgresql
</pre>

<p>Create the database:</p>
<pre>
sudo -u postgres psql
</pre>

<p>Inside the PostgreSQL prompt (you'll see <code>postgres=#</code>):</p>
<pre>
CREATE USER bankos WITH PASSWORD 'pick_a_strong_db_password_here';
CREATE DATABASE bankos OWNER bankos;
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE bankos TO bankos;
\q
</pre>

<div class="important">
    <strong>SAVE</strong> this database password &mdash; you'll need it for .env files.
</div>

<h3>3.5 Install Redis</h3>
<pre>
apt install -y redis-server
systemctl enable redis-server
systemctl start redis-server
</pre>

<h3>3.6 Install Nginx</h3>
<pre>
apt install -y nginx
systemctl enable nginx
</pre>

<h3>3.7 Install Node.js 20 (for Vite builds)</h3>
<pre>
curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | bash -
apt install -y nodejs
</pre>

<h3>3.8 Install Supervisor</h3>
<pre>
apt install -y supervisor
systemctl enable supervisor
</pre>

<h3>3.9 Install Git</h3>
<pre>
apt install -y git
</pre>

<!-- PHASE 4 -->
<div class="page-break"></div>
<h1 id="phase4">5. Phase 4 &mdash; Upload Your Code</h1>

<h3>Option A: Using GitHub (Recommended)</h3>

<h4>On your local Windows machine, push each app to a private GitHub repo:</h4>
<pre>
# In each app folder locally:
cd "c:/laragon/www/antigravity codes/bankos"
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/bankos.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main

# Repeat for bankos-portal and bankos-superadmin
</pre>

<h4>On the server (SSH as deploy user):</h4>
<pre>
ssh deploy@YOUR_SERVER_IP
</pre>
<pre>
sudo mkdir -p /var/www
sudo chown deploy:deploy /var/www
cd /var/www
</pre>
<pre>
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/bankos.git
# Enter your GitHub username and Personal Access Token (not password)
# Generate token at: github.com &rarr; Settings &rarr; Developer settings
#   &rarr; Personal access tokens &rarr; Tokens (classic) &rarr; Generate
# Give it "repo" scope

git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/bankos-portal.git
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/bankos-superadmin.git
</pre>

<p>Save credentials so you don't have to re-enter them:</p>
<pre>
git config --global credential.helper store
</pre>

<h3>Option B: Direct Upload (No GitHub)</h3>
<p>If you don't want to use GitHub, use <strong>FileZilla</strong> (free FTP/SFTP client):</p>
<ol>
    <li>Download FileZilla from filezilla-project.org</li>
    <li>Connect: <strong>Host:</strong> YOUR_SERVER_IP, <strong>Username:</strong> deploy, <strong>Password:</strong> your deploy password, <strong>Port:</strong> 22 (SFTP)</li>
    <li>Navigate to <code>/var/www/</code> on the server</li>
    <li>Upload all 3 app folders there</li>
</ol>

<!-- PHASE 5 -->
<div class="page-break"></div>
<h1 id="phase5">6. Phase 5 &mdash; Configure Each App</h1>

<h3>5.1 Set up bankos (Admin Portal)</h3>
<pre>
cd /var/www/bankos

composer install --no-dev --optimize-autoloader

cp .env.example .env
nano .env
</pre>

<p>Set these values in .env:</p>
<pre>
APP_NAME=bankOS
APP_ENV=production
APP_DEBUG=false
APP_URL=https://admin.yourdomain.com

DB_CONNECTION=pgsql
DB_HOST=127.0.0.1
DB_PORT=5432
DB_DATABASE=bankos
DB_USERNAME=bankos
DB_PASSWORD=your_db_password_here

CACHE_DRIVER=redis
SESSION_DRIVER=redis
QUEUE_CONNECTION=redis
REDIS_HOST=127.0.0.1

MAIL_MAILER=smtp
MAIL_HOST=smtp-relay.brevo.com
MAIL_PORT=587
MAIL_USERNAME=your_brevo_login
MAIL_PASSWORD=your_brevo_smtp_key
MAIL_FROM_ADDRESS=noreply@yourdomain.com
MAIL_FROM_NAME="bankOS"
</pre>

<p>Save: <code>Ctrl+O</code>, <code>Enter</code>, <code>Ctrl+X</code></p>

<pre>
php artisan key:generate
php artisan migrate --force
php artisan config:cache
php artisan route:cache
php artisan view:cache
npm ci &amp;&amp; npm run build

sudo chown -R www-data:www-data storage bootstrap/cache
sudo chmod -R 775 storage bootstrap/cache
</pre>

<h3>5.2 Set up bankos-portal (Customer Portal)</h3>
<pre>
cd /var/www/bankos-portal

composer install --no-dev --optimize-autoloader

cp .env.example .env
nano .env
</pre>

<pre>
APP_NAME="bankOS Portal"
APP_ENV=production
APP_DEBUG=false
APP_URL=https://app.yourdomain.com

DB_CONNECTION=pgsql
DB_HOST=127.0.0.1
DB_PORT=5432
DB_DATABASE=bankos
DB_USERNAME=bankos
DB_PASSWORD=your_db_password_here

CACHE_DRIVER=redis
SESSION_DRIVER=redis
QUEUE_CONNECTION=redis
REDIS_HOST=127.0.0.1

MAIL_MAILER=smtp
MAIL_HOST=smtp-relay.brevo.com
MAIL_PORT=587
MAIL_USERNAME=your_brevo_login
MAIL_PASSWORD=your_brevo_smtp_key
MAIL_FROM_ADDRESS=noreply@yourdomain.com
MAIL_FROM_NAME="bankOS"
</pre>

<pre>
php artisan key:generate
php artisan config:cache
php artisan route:cache
php artisan view:cache
npm ci &amp;&amp; npm run build

sudo chown -R www-data:www-data storage bootstrap/cache
sudo chmod -R 775 storage bootstrap/cache
</pre>

<h3>5.3 Set up bankos-superadmin</h3>
<pre>
cd /var/www/bankos-superadmin

composer install --no-dev --optimize-autoloader

cp .env.example .env
nano .env
</pre>

<pre>
APP_NAME="bankOS SuperAdmin"
APP_ENV=production
APP_DEBUG=false
APP_URL=https://super.yourdomain.com

DB_CONNECTION=pgsql
DB_HOST=127.0.0.1
DB_PORT=5432
DB_DATABASE=bankos
DB_USERNAME=bankos
DB_PASSWORD=your_db_password_here

CACHE_DRIVER=redis
SESSION_DRIVER=redis
QUEUE_CONNECTION=redis
REDIS_HOST=127.0.0.1
</pre>

<pre>
php artisan key:generate
php artisan config:cache
php artisan route:cache
